The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for quantum control, specifically for parameter optimization in noisy quantum systems. This falls under the intersection of quantum computing and machine learning, making cs.LG the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of differential evolution algorithms, which falls under optimization and search algorithms, making cs.ET and cs.SY likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heuristics and adaptive selection, which are common in artificial intelligence and neural networks, making cs.AI and cs.NE likely sub-categories as well.
